          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I have been very disappointed with the way the school keeps increasing its fees every year. The fee structure has become too high, and there is no transparency or proper communication regarding these hikes. Many parents, including myself, have raised concerns, but unfortunately, no one seems to listen or take any action.\n\nIt’s disheartening because the academics and facilities do not justify the constant fee increase. My child is currently studying here, but I have decided to change the school next year due to this ongoing issue. I hope the management pays attention to the parents’ feedback and takes steps to make education more affordable and fair.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "St. Xaviers High School - Ghasola,Sector 49"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Anonymous"
          },
          "datePublished": "2025-10-08",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "3",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Teachers are good till primary. Middle and Senior, not so good. There have been couple of instances where students were verbally abused by teachers. \nManagement is very money minded and fee hike is 10% avg. They also do not follow government guidelines for fee hike.\nCampus and facilities are great but of no use to students as they occasionally get to use them. School mostly encourages post school hour engagement through paid sports academy on school grounds. They very conveniently take credit for students preforming well when they have barely contributed in their developement.\nAnnual and sports day are another money minting opportunity for school where they charge unreasonable amount for useless costumes. Even student participation is unfair as mostly teachers kids are promoted. Their response to most parents grievance is 'You can take your kid out'. Every year there is mass exodus of students which is beneficial for the school as it generates more revenue in form of admission fees. The current principal is 4th in row in 7 years. Staff retention is much worse as senior classes sometimes dont even have crucial teachers in board classes.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
